# Title: ETW Logging Tamper In .NET Processes Via CommandLine
# Author: Roberto Rodriguez (Cyb3rWard0g), OTR (Open Threat Research)
# Date: 2020-05-02
# Level: high
# Description: Detects changes to environment variables related to ETW logging via the CommandLine.
# This could indicate potential adversaries stopping ETW providers recording loaded .NET assemblies.
# MITRE Tactic: Uncategorized
# Tags: attack.defense-impairment, attack.t1685
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_susp_etw_modification_cmdline.yml
# False Positives:
#   - Unlikely

CommandLine IN ("*COMPlus_ETWEnabled*", "*COMPlus_ETWFlags*")